 tracts only","Lateral corticospinal and corticobulbar tracts only","Anterior corticospinal and corticobulbar tracts only","Both corticospinal tracts and corticobulbar tract","Anterior corticospinal tract and rubrospinal tract only"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eboth corticospinal tracts and corticobulbar tract\u003C/strong\u003E pass through both the corona radiata and internal capsule. These pathways originate in the motor cortex and descend through these white matter structures before continuing to their targets.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe corona radiata is a fan-shaped white matter structure that contains both ascending and descending fibre tracts. These fibres converge to form the internal capsule, a compact white matter bundle between the thalamus and basal ganglia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral and anterior corticospinal tracts only\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the corticobulbar tract which also passes through these structures\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral corticospinal and corticobulbar tracts only\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the anterior corticospinal tract\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnterior corticospinal and corticobulbar tracts only\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the lateral corticospinal tract\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnterior corticospinal tract and rubrospinal tract only\u003C/strong\u003E - The rubrospinal tract does not pass through these structures, and this omits other major tracts\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The corticospinal tracts (lateral and anterior) and corticobulbar tract all pass through both the corona radiata and internal capsule.","The corona radiata is a fan-shaped white matter structure containing ascending and descending pathways.","The internal capsule is a compact white matter bundle between the thalamus and basal ganglia that contains major motor pathways."],"references":["Javed K, Reddy V, Lui F. Neuroanatomy, Lateral Corticospinal Tract. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534818/","Smith AC, Weber KA 2nd, O\u0027Dell DR, Parrish TB, Wasielewski M, Elliott JM. Lateral Corticospinal Tract Damage Correlates With Motor Output in Incomplete Spinal Cord Injury. Arch Phys Med Rehabil. 2018 Apr;99(4):660-666. doi: 10.1016/j.apmr.2017.10.002. Epub 2017 Oct 26. PMID: 29107041; PMCID: PMC5871547.","Bhardwaj N, Yadala S. Neuroanatomy, Corticobulbar Tract. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32310351.","Hall, J. E., \u0026 Hall, M. E. (2020). Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book: Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60909"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16516"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60909","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60909"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T19:27:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T19:28:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9207"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75400"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{